<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06279111 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06279111 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  FASHION; COMPANY; STOCK; DECREASE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  L.A. Gear Inc. announced an $11.4 million net loss for the third quarter onFriday and predicted continued hard times for the struggling maker of athleticand casual shoes.;   The company, plagued by slow sales, said it is reviewingits operations and expects write-offs and other adjustments, which will have&quot;significant adverse effect&quot; on its fourth-quarter and year-end earnings.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  L.A. GEAR POSTS $11.4 MILLION LOSS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Earnings  </MEMO><TEXT>     For the third quarter, the company lost 57 cents per share on net sales of$173.7 million. That compares with net income of $14.2 million, or 71 centsper share on net sales of $300 million in the same quarter a year ago.;   InAugust, L.A. Gear reached a new agreement with bankers for a $200 millioncredit line, enabling the firm to enter into a bailout plan with TrefoilCapital Investors, a group led by Roy Disney, a nephew of Walt Disney.;  Under terms of the deal, Trefoil purchased a 30 percent stake in L.A. Gear for$100 million.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Los Angeles  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911005  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  16F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  163  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday, October 5, 199100279111,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>